column5: Is awsome , since i put the boat away . Today and tomorrow realy looks good for any one wanting to give it a try ........ darn it !
You never put the boat away Skip, if there's any chance you'll want to get back on the water before the season closes.  Nice weather this time of year isn't the least bit unusual.

I know Lew , i had a mess of snow equipment to get ready and i kept putting off and off and with that snow here last week i had to give in . There is another boat out back that i bought this summer ...... aw for get it ............lol .
~~~~Saturday out of Pephpherlaw winds at 20K out of the South temp 10+

Spent this after noon working in the shop , wished every minute i could get done quick and go do you know what , O' well theres all next year , boys that was a nice day . Did any one make it out on Simcoe today ?
Me thinks,the river will be visited this weekend.Or that could change to sitting in the stand. Two,many options.
To warm to sit in the stand this weekend were in the 70's F.   Art

Brian i'am not sure what season opened up north of Barrie this week , but off in the distance thru out the day you can hear hundreds of shots going off at differant times , about every fifthteen minutes it seems . What ever it is that there shooting at must be awfull hard to take down cause one shot dose'nt seem to be doing it . I was laughing to my self after a while thinking that what ever it is must look like they took a paper punch to it by now . The only thing i could come up with is some one has to be out target practicing .
Likey ducks and geese. A box of shells doesnt last long if theres lots flying and you shoot like me lol
The only thing we have here is bush all around us , no rivers or lakes that close . But it did sound the same as opening day for duck on the St Lawrence River .......... lol .
Theres a gun range near you that the OPP use.Thats probly what yer hearing.

Got ya Brian . Been here for twenty four years and never heard it before . I found out today where it is , Three roads over to the east of us , amazing how far the sound travels . Probably be another 24 years before i ever notice it again .
Heading out shortly to do some shore fishing for jumbos.Still a while before hardwater and there is still some good opportunities out there!
Good luck , sure is a nice morning for it .
